# Python Development Standards

## 🐍 Code Quality Standards
- Use Python 3.11+ for all scripts
- Follow PEP 8 style guidelines
- Use type hints for all functions
- Implement comprehensive error handling
- Add docstrings to all functions and classes

## 📦 Dependencies
- Core: [requirements_integrated.txt](mdc:requirements_integrated.txt)
- Key packages: datasets, numpy, anthropic, fastapi, uvicorn
- Use virtual environments for isolation

## 📁 Script Structure
- All scripts in [scripts/](mdc:scripts/) directory
- Use shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env python3`
- Include encoding: `# -*- coding: utf-8 -*-`
- Add comprehensive logging

## 🚀 Performance Guidelines
- Use async/await for I/O operations
- Implement streaming for large datasets
- Use memory-efficient processing
- Add progress bars for long operations

## 🧪 Testing Requirements
- Unit tests for core functions
- Integration tests for workflows
- Error scenario testing
- Performance benchmarking
